				<td colspan="2"><span>Not trying to be offensive to anyone, but It is absolutely ridiculous to think that the reason stuff doesn't get fixed is because the devs are lazy and/or incompetent. These guys have a million things to do and I'm 99% positive work very hard at their jobs.
<br />

<br />
Now it is possible that in order to make more dough, Sony understaffs their development team, but that doesnt mean the devs aren't working hard. Anyone who has development of any kind will realize that you can only get so much done in a certain period of time. When there aren't enough bodies to get the work done, even when you work crazy hours, the work jus doesn't get done. pretty simple.
<br />

<br />
Sure there are lots of outstanding issues that have been outstanding for a very long time...  but wouldn't you say it's more likely that they are fixing OTHER more important global issues, such as ppl losing levels in OOW and crap like that ?
