				<td colspan="2"><span>The guy who made that joke website missed the point entirely. Its not the developers who are the bad guys (although they DO have some blame, why does a change in one place break so many other things?). Its the whole company. They're failing all over the place. The designers are pushing the game, and us, into these boring encounters that hardly anyone enjoys. The customer service reps dont talk to the players. The devs aren't being careful with their coding, and the QA staff, if there are any, aren't testing. And at the very top, the senior management is watching it all happen, even dramatic things like sit-ins and mass protest mailings, and ignoring it all. Everywhere you look there are problems.
<br />

<br />
What if your cable company behaved this way? Or television stations? Or the movie theatre you bring your dates to? Or any consumer oriented traditional business? I tell you what would happen. You would switch to another company, or turn them off. You would stop paying. 
<br />

<br />
In the end, OoW will probably spell the end for SoE. They've pissed off too many people too close to a major upgrade in competition. For a long time they've enjoyed a substantial advantage because they were first out of the gate with the genre. Times have changed though. They can no longer afford to behave as if we have no other options. As long as they do, they will be priming the market to replace them.
<br />

<br />
I for one retired the day after OoW came out. I had 3 accounts, for a total of 45 dollars or so a month that I cancelled. At first, I did it to send a message that I was unhappy. I thought, well, if they see a bunch of people quitting, maybe they'll change their ways. Several weeks later, though, I now think won't go back even if they do fix things. I started playing the game because it was fun. It was challenging, and I enjoyed the content. Lately though, the game isn't fun, it's infuriating. Anger and frustration isn't something I am willing to pay an entertainment company for. 
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
